comments: Wide channel with fast flowing water. Many larger fish were caught (>200mm). Some deep pools spotted that could be suitable for overwintering. Cobbles and boulders in stream ptoviding cover. Moderate habitat value. . 12:26:06

Very wide channel but not a lot of cover from overhanging veg or crown closure. Mostly cobbles and boulders in stream. Some deep pools with fish found. All bull trout except one which was WCT. Only trace amounts of woody debris. Moderate value habitat. . 12:12:56

Moderate habitat quality. Fast flowing water with rapids and a few cascades that are about 0.6-0.7m in height. Could block passage of smaller fish. Lots of large woody debris changing the stream course and leading to small cascades. Wide channel with cover from boulders and cobbles. Deep pools in outlet to cascades. Some areas with gravels suitable for spawning. Good amount of cover from overhanging veg. . 14:06:36

Medium value habitat. Frequent large Woody debris jams between 40 and 70 cm in height. Frequent small cascade sections of to 10% and up to 3 to 5 m long. Numerous sections with Apple quantity of travels suitable for resident and fluvial WCT. Surveyed in a downstream direction with the bottom end of the site at the first ford.. 14:32:07

Moderate habitat value. Steep gradient with some cascades less than a meter in height. A few deep pools that could be ideal for resident fish. No fish caught in site. Boulders and cobbles the dominant substrate. No gravels areas suitable for spawning. Confined stream with cover from vegetation. . 12:42:00

Moderate habitat value. Steep gradient with some cascades less than a meter in height. A few deep pools that could be ideal for resident fish. No fish caught in site. Boulders and cobbles the dominant substrate. No gravels areas suitable for spawning. Confined stream with covet from vegetation. . 11:26:43

Bottom approximately 50 m of the site also functions as a side channel of the Big Horn Creek main stem. Some of the flows in the lowe section may have be influenced by ground water from the main stem.. 10:33:46

Stream was dry throughout reach five so surveyors worked their way back to where the water began and worked 300m upstream. Nupqu 1 GPS waypoint Reach5weigertWetted. Took 3 channel width measurements within that 300m filled out stream card info.  . 13:48:40

High value habitat. Abundant gravels suitable for residential and fluvial WCT and BT. Few pools suitable for overwintering. Top of site is 7m high cascade waterfall definitely not passable in an upstream direction. 12:12:58

Electrofishing site was the first 400 to 450 m and then approximately 100 m further was assessed to gather more habitat characteristics. Most fish captured were observed by the crew before they were captured and all were adults.          . 12:20:59
